Instruction: With the PSU open and the good 12 V battery installed, use a multimeter in continuity/ohms mode to test the entire series path from the battery positive lug to the common node that feeds the green LED/resistor and the positive output cable terminal. Probe from battery + to each intermediate pad/trace/component (including any fuse link, thin PCB track, switch, or connector) to locate where continuity is lost and identify the exact open point.
